text: Florence (O'odham: S-auppag) is a town, southeast of Phoenix, in Pinal County of Arizona, United States. Florence is the county seat of Pinal County. It is one of the oldest towns in that county and is regarded as a National Historic District. The population of Florence was 26,785 at the 2020 census. ==References== Category:County seats in Arizona Category:Towns in Arizona
title: Florence, Arizona
